SIMPLE: cobaltous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cobaltous
<hw>Co*balt"ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, derived from, or containing, cobalt; -- said esp. of
cobalt compounds in which the metal has its lower valence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cobaltous chloride</b></col>, <cd>a crystalline compound,
<chform>CoCl2</chform>, of a pale rose color when hydrous, blue when
dehydrated. Its solution is used for a sympathetic ink, the writing
being nearly colorless when dried in the air, owing to absorbed
moisture, and becoming bright blue when warmed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cobbing</ent>⟦br⟧
